title.narrative: Program to Extend Scholarship and Training to Achieve Sustainable Impacts (PRESTASI II)

description.narrative: (Indonesia): Under the U.S.-Indonesia Comprehensive Partnership, the U.S. and Indonesian Governments committed to strengthening and expanding Indonesia's professional and technical workforce, especially by providing Indonesian professionals with greater educational opportunities.Through this IM, USAID provides Indonesian professionals with higher education opportunities in Indonesia and the United States. Through these opportunities, it is expected that public and private sector professionals will gain valuable the technical and leadership skills and apply them in ways that benefit Indonesian economic and governance interests. USAID will invest in sustainable alliances between U.S. and Indonesian educational institutions to promote cultural, technical, and management exchanges. These alliances will also provide short-term training opportunities. Investments will provide training for Indonesian lecturers focused on academic capacity and scientific research. In FY 2014 short-term technical training in the U.S., third country and in Indonesia will be provided. Participants will be identified through USAID and Indonesian partner priorities.Expected results through the IM include:-Creation of a strong cadre of leaders and managers who will apply new knowledge and skills within priority development sectors.-Strengthened institutions including GOI ministries and other priority public and private sector institutions and organizations.-More efficient, transparent, and accountable practices in managing resources across sectors leading to better service delivery.-Increased goodwill and cultural understanding among Indonesians as a result of academic study in the United States.-More Indonesian leaders holding advanced degrees (Master's and Ph.D.'s) from U.S. and Indonesian institutions of higher education.-More women and individuals from disadvantaged and/or underrepresented geographic areas participating in the program.
